    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style of artistic production in Falerii now present day Cività Castellana in central Italy.  Known mainly as a significant center of red-figure pottery during the 4th century BCE, works of art include red-figure vases produced by the Aurora Painter and the Nazzano Painter.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000045295/Cook, Greek Painted Pottery (1966)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere al estilo de producción artística en Falerii hoy en día Cività Castellana en Italia central. Conocido principalmente como un importante centro de cerámica de figura roja durante el siglo IV A.C, las obras de arte incluyen vasos de figura roja producidos por el Pintor Aurora y el Pintor Nazzano.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de stijl van kunstvoorwerpen zoals voortgebracht in Falerii, het tegenwoordige Civita Castellana in Centraal-Italië, dat voornamelijk bekend is als belangrijk centrum van roodfigurig aardewerk in de 4e eeuw v. Chr. Tot de gevonden kunstvoorwerpen behoren roodfigurige vazen die zijn gemaakt door de Schilder van Aurora en de Schilder van Nazzano.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052614/Brijder, De Etrusken (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指在法勒里（Falerii），亦即現今位於義大利中部的奇維塔卡斯特拉納（Cività Castellana）所發展出的藝術製作風格。西元前四世紀時，主要為出產紅彩陶器（或譯紅陶red-figure pottery）的重鎮而聞名，製作的藝術品包括奧羅拉（Aurora）與那札諾（Nazzano）兩地的藝術家所繪製的紅彩陶瓶。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
